						               													<description>The sequel in the popular series The Only Word - now on dice!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Call for your imagination and think of The Only One Word to describe several different images on the dice. It is a fast game, in which everyone plays for themself. Very compact, with handy components and easy rules, for any number of players &amp;ndash; it is a party game which works great even on picnics or trips, as you do not need a table to play it.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Roll 9 special dice with images and put them on the colored game board, right in the box. Each player is dealt an equal number of challenge cards. The color code on the challenge cards indicates the dice on the game board. The task is to find a one-word association to describe (or bridge) 2 or even 3 images of your secret challenge task. The other players should crack the clue and guess right your dice. The fastest player to guess and the Cluegiver each discard 1 challenge card. The winner is the first player who got rid of the challenge cards.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game is great fun! It sharpens your wits, hones your imagination and helps you to tune up with your friends.&amp;#10;The game also has cooperative and solo modes.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
